<FrameLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context="admin.example.com.SubTopics.Prob.BALLS">

    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:focusable="false"
        android:visibility="visible">


        <RelativeLayout
            android:id="@+id/rl1"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_marginBottom="500dp"
            android:layout_marginEnd="2dp"
            android:layout_marginRight="4dp"
            android:layout_marginTop="30dp"
            android:minHeight="50dp">


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv1"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_toEndOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:layout_toRightOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question  1 :\n
A 30 litres milk-water mixture contains 50% milk. How much pure milk need to be added to this mixture to make the mixture 30% water?

\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv11"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@+id/tv1"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_toEndOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:layout_toRightOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solutions –
30 litres mixture contains 15 litres of water. When milk added to this, quantity of water will remain same (i.e. 15 l)\n
Let x l of pure milk to be added, then\n
30% of (30+x) = 15\n
Solve, x = 20 \n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121" />

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div1"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv11" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv2"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div1"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 2:\n
A can contains 40 litres of milk at Rs 3.5 per litre. How much water must be added to this can so that the cost of milk reduces to Rs 2 per litre?
\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv22"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv2"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Milk(40 litres)   \t         Water(x litres)\n
3.5            \t \t                         0.2\n
2             \t \t                          1.5\n
Ratio = 2 : 1.5 = 4 : 3\n
so 4/3 = 40/x\n
solve, x = 30\n
\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div2"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv22" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv3"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div2"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 3:\n
A can contains 60 litres of milk. 10 litres of this milk is taken out and replaced with water. This process is repeated again. Find the amount of remaining milk in the mixture?

"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv33"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv3"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Remaining milk = 60 [1 – (10/60)]^2\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div3"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv33" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv4"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div3"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 4.\n
A can contains milk and water in the ratio 3:1. A part of this mixture is replaced with milk, and now the new ratio of milk to water is 15:4.What proportion of original mixture had been replaced by milk?

"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv44"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv4"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Let total original quantity = x litres, Let y litres replaced.\n
After y litres of mixture drawn out,\n
Milk = [3/(3+1)] * x – [3/(3+1)] * y\n
Water = [1/(3+1)] * x – [1/(3+1)] * y\n
Now y litres of milk poured in can. Milk becomes (3/4)*x – (3/4)*y +y = (3/4)*x +(1/4)*y\n
Now [(3/4)*x +(1/4)*y] / [(1/4)*x – (1/4)*y] = 15/4\n
Solve, y = (3/19)* x\n
So 3/19 of original mixture removed. \n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div4"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv44" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv5"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div4"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 5.\n
A mixture contains A and B in the ratio 2 : 5. 7 litres of mixture is replaced by 18 litres of A and the new ratio becomes 8 : 11 respectively. What is the amount of A present in the original mixture?
\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv55"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv5"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
A = 2x, B = 5x\n
After 7 litres draw out:\n
A = 2x – (2/7)*7 = 2x – 2 , B = 5x – (5/7)*7 = 5x – 5\n
After 18 l of A put back, A = (2x – 2) + 18 = 2x +16\n
So (2x+16)/(5x-5) = 8/11\n
Solve, x = 12\n
So A = 2x = 2*12\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div5"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv55" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv6"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div5"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 6.\n
How many kilograms of wheat at Rs 42 per kg be mixed with 25 kg of wheat at Rs 24 per kg so that on selling the mixture at Rs 40 per kg, there is a gain of 25%?

\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv66"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv6"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Let x kg of wheat at Rs 42 per kg be mixed
SP = 40, gain% = 25%, so CP = (100/125) * 40 = Rs 32
So
1st wheat(x kg)      \t          2nd wheat(25 kg)\n
42          \t     \t                                24\n
8          \t       \t                                10\n
So 8/10 = x/25\n
Solve, x = 20 \n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div6"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv66" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv7"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div6"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 7.\n
A 132 litres of mixture contains milk and water in the ratio 5 : 7. How much milk need to be added to this mixture so that the new ratio is 13 : 11 respectively?

\n"                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv77"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv7"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Milk in original = (5/12) * 132 = 55 l, so water = 132 – 55 = 77 l\n
Let x l of milk to be added, so\n
(55+x)/77 = 13/11\n
Solve, x = 36\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div7"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv77" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv8"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div7"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 8.\n
1st mixture contains 30% zinc and rest copper and a 2nd mixture contains 20% zinc and rest copper. Some quantity is taken out of 1st mixture and twice this quantity is taken from 2nd mixture and mixed in a bottle. Find the ratio of copper to zinc in the bottle.

\n"               android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv88"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv8"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solutions:\n
Let x litres taken from 1st mixture, then 2x litres from 2nd mixture.\n So ratio of copper to zinc =\n
70% of x + 80% of 2x : 30% of x + 20% of 2x \n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div8"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv88" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv9"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div8"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 9.\n
A Container contains 192 liter of Milk. A seller draws out x% of Milk and replaced it with the same quantity of water. He repeated the same process for 3 times. And thus Milk content in the mixture is only 81 liter. Then how much percent he withdraw every time?
"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv99"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv9"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
81 = 192(1-x/100)³\n
x = 25/n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div9"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv99" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv10"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div9"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 10.\n
A jar contains ‘x’ liters of Milk, a seller withdraws 25 liter of it and sells it at Rs.20 per liter. He then replaces it water. He repeated the process total three times. Every time while selling he reduces selling price by Rs.2. After this process Milk left in the mixture is only 108 liters so he decided to sell the entire Mixture at Rs. 15 per liter. Then how much profit did he earned if bought Milk at Rs.20 per liter?

\n"                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv100"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv10"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Seller sells Milk at Rs.20,18 and 16 respectively for three times\n
= 25*(20+18+16) = 1350\n
108 = x(1-25/100) 3\n
x =256 liter\n
He sold entire 256 at Rs.15 =256*15 = 3840\n
Cost price = 256*20 = 5120\n
profit = 5190-5120 = 70\n\n \n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div10"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv100" />


        </RelativeLayout>

    </ScrollView>


</FrameLayout>
